                    Donating blood is an incredibly impactful act that is both simple and time-efficient. The entire donation process, from the moment you arrive at the donation center until the time you leave, typically takes around 30 minutes. The actual blood donation itself lasts an average of just 8 to 10 minutes. Let's walk through the steps involved in this seamless process, ensuring that your contribution is both convenient and rewarding:
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-lg-8 content">
                    <h3>Before Donating Blood</h3>
                    <p class="fst-italic" style="text-align: justify">
                        To ensure a smooth and successful blood donation experience, it is essential to take certain precautions beforehand. Prior to donating blood,
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li class="fst-italic" style="text-align: justify"><i class="bi bi-check-circle"></i> it is recommended that you consume a substantial meal to maintain your energy levels.  </li>
                        <li class="fst-italic" style="text-align: justify"><i class="bi bi-check-circle"></i> Additionally, it is crucial to stay well-hydrated, especially in warm weather conditions. In the 3 hours leading up to your donation appointment, aim to drink at least 3 to 4 generous glasses of water or juice. </li>
                    </ul>
                    <p class="fst-italic" style="text-align: justify">
                        By following these guidelines, you will help ensure that your body is adequately prepared for the donation process, promoting a positive experience for both you and the recipient of your life-saving contribution.
                    </p>
                    <br/>
                    <h3>Registration of Donor</h3>
                    <p class="fst-italic" style="text-align: justify">
                        To streamline the donation process and ensure accurate record-keeping, our dedicated volunteers or staff members will guide you through the registration process. They will kindly request you to complete a form that includes essential information such as your contact details and medical history. This step is crucial as it allows us to maintain a comprehensive record of your donation and helps us ensure your eligibility to donate blood. Rest assured that all the information you provide will be handled with the utmost confidentiality and used solely for the purpose of facilitating the donation process. Your cooperation in filling out the form will greatly contribute to a smooth and efficient experience, enabling us to serve you and others in need more effectively.
                    </p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="col-lg-4">
                    <a href="">
                        <img src="assets/img/web/register_donor.png" alt="Donor Registration" class="img-fluid">
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
