                    <p class="fst-italic" style="text-align: justify">
                        Once you have generously donated blood, we want to ensure that you have a comfortable and smooth recovery. After the donation process, we invite you to take some time to relax and enjoy light refreshments for approximately 15-20 minutes before you leave. This allows your body to adjust and ensures you feel rejuvenated before continuing with your day.
                        It's important to note that your body has a remarkable ability to restore its blood volume within 24-48 hours after the donation. Your system works diligently to replenish the donated blood, ensuring that you maintain optimal health and well-being.
                        <br/>
                        To aid in your quick recovery, we recommend following a few simple guidelines.
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li class="fst-italic" style="text-align: justify"><i class="bi bi-check-circle"></i>Firstly, it's crucial to stay hydrated by drinking plenty of fluids such as water and fruit juice. However, we kindly ask that you avoid consuming alcohol for at least 8 hours after your donation, as it may interfere with the recovery process.</li>
                        <li class="fst-italic" style="text-align: justify"><i class="bi bi-check-circle"></i>Additionally, we advise refraining from engaging in any strenuous activities or heavy lifting with the arm from which blood was drawn for a period of 24 hours. This precaution helps to prevent any potential discomfort or strain during the initial healing phase.</li>
                        <li class="fst-italic" style="text-align: justify"><i class="bi bi-check-circle"></i>While it is rare, if you experience any form of illness or discomfort after your donation, please don't hesitate to seek assistance from the doctor in charge. Your well-being is of utmost importance to us, and our medical professionals are readily available to address any concerns and provide appropriate guidance.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p class="fst-italic" style="text-align: justify">We appreciate your selfless act of donating blood and making a significant difference in the lives of others. Your generosity and commitment to saving lives are invaluable, and we are truly grateful for your support.</p>
